          I know there have been an annoying amount of posts from me today but I'm in a posting mood and OH WAIT I OWN THE PLACE so anyway I don't know if any of you remember but I used Blogger's profiling service to try to find somebody around the Arlington area to chill with while I spend the summer here.  So I found <a href="http://www.jess3.com">Jesse</a>, who is not only in the area but is also a professional webdesigner. I decided to email <a href="http://www.jess3.com">Jesse</a> and ask if there was any interest in telling a newb to the area any cool things to check out.<br /><br />We passed emails back and forth for a week or so but yesterday was eye opening for me. Here is a conversation I had today with one of E3R's posters about the outcome.<blockquote><a href="http://www.blogger.com/profile/3586520">Ninjaboie</a>: anyways you ever hear back from that web designer girl you emailed?<br />me: lol yes<br />me: morgan was mad at me because she thought that the girl was hot<br /><a href="http://www.blogger.com/profile/3586520">Ninjaboie</a>: ..oh..jelousy thing?<br />me: and I was thinkin 'whatever' I just want to hang with somebody<br /><a href="http://www.blogger.com/profile/3586520">Ninjaboie</a>: right.<br />me: so <a href="http://www.jess3.com">Jesse</a> and I have been sending emails back and forth for a while now and yesterday she IMs me<br /><a href="http://www.blogger.com/profile/3586520">Ninjaboie</a>: makes sense I mean you know like nobody out there man<br />me: offers to take me to a bar I decline because I'm not 21.<br />me: and I say 'nevertheless, you have some serious skill!'<br />me: she says 'thank you, sir'<br />me: and I say...<br />me: "no problem, ma'am." Big mistake, dude. <br />me: she says: "what?"<br />me: "Joe, I'm a guy."<br /><a href="http://www.blogger.com/profile/3586520">Ninjaboie</a>: ...<br /><a href="http://www.blogger.com/profile/3586520">Ninjaboie</a>: lmao</blockquote>Since then, I have tried to make contact <a href="http://www.jess3.com">Jesse</a> and he's been cool about the whole thing. I actually like the guy's site so much that I might be linking him here soon. Anybody else have a similar situation to comment on?<br />
