          My first blog in a while.  Well, i did have one a little over a week ago, several paragraphs long that magically dissappeared.  Blah!  That's what i say.<br /><br />Anyway, off to Italy tomorrow for a 2 week long excursion w/ fam.  Looking forward to finding ways to sneak off and legally drink.  I'm hoping the language barrier won't be too much of a problem.  Just need to learn the italian word for 'drink' and i think i'm set.  Thought i'd do something i've never tried before, and that's logging my travels across Italy.  Man, i went to England and France 2 summers back; now i can hardly remember where i went while i was there.  Maybe a log will help keep the memories alive and burning.<br /><br />In my last post that never came to be i wrote something about how Marvel is superior to DC in practically everyway.  I see this conversation still lingers, so i figured i'd add my 2 cents.  Marvels characters are just easier to relate to than DC's.  Marvel heros are struggling students working a superhero night job; DC heros are superpowered aliens with the concept of Justice infused into their brains.  Now who can i identify with more?  A struggling student, or an allmighty self righteous alien?     DC, on the other had, has Vertigo; which is a seperate line of comics set apart from the DC universe and geared specifically towards adults.  They've published some of the best adult comics ever, such as Sandman, Preacher, Hellblazer, and 100 Bullets.  It's great stuff; def worth checking out to all my fellow geeks.<br /><br />That's all i really feel like saying right now.  Ah, Tuuk, i'd love to get ahold of those Radiohead B-sides you mentioned a while back.  My email's BigD4587@aol.com, assuming the offer still stands.  <br /><br />Well then....WHAMMY!<br />
